The paper proposes a novel approach for access control mechanisms in healthcare systems using Blockchain technology. This involves creating a tree structure consisting of a main chain linked with the patient's identity and one or several subchains for storing critical data. This work involves aspects of cryptography (cs.CR), database systems (cs.DB), distributed computing (cs.DC), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and software engineering (cs.SE).
